{
  "texts": [
    "A major limitation of DNNs is their complex nature, which makes them challenging to interpret, and they may involve meticulous hyperparameter tuning (Vamathevan et al. 2019; Nag et al. 2022).",
    "CNNs are suited for image and grid-structured data.",
    "They employ convolutional layers to detect local patterns.",
    "CNNs are constructed with several key components: convolutional layers, pooling layers, and densely connected layers.",
    "The network begins with an input layer, followed by convolutional layers that extract features from the input data."
  ]
}